Honam Petrochemical Said to Be Processing LPG at Ethylene Plants

-- B y   S a n g i m   H a n
-- 
2011-04-25T06:33:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-25/honam-petrochemical-said-to-be-processing-lpg-at-ethylene-plants.html
Honam Petrochemical Corp. (011170)  is
running about 10 percent of its Yeosu and Daesan ethylene plants
in  South Korea  on liquefied petroleum gas, according to a
company official.  The plants have reduced the amount of naphtha used as
feedstock in a move to counter rising prices, said the official,
who declined to be identified because the information is
confidential.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sangim Han in Seoul at 
 sihan@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Amit Prakash at 
 aprakash1@bloomberg.net  